4526 /**Function*************************************************************
4527 
4528  Synopsis [Prepares the data for MSOPs of 4-variable functions.]
4529 
4530  Description []
4531 
4532  SideEffects []
4533 
4534  SeeAlso []
4535 
4536 ***********************************************************************/
4537 void Cnf_ReadMsops( char ** ppSopSizes, char *** ppSops )
4538 {
4539  unsigned uMasks[4][2] = {
4540  { 0x5555, 0xAAAA },
4541  { 0x3333, 0xCCCC },
4542  { 0x0F0F, 0xF0F0 },
4543  { 0x00FF, 0xFF00 }
4544  };
4545  char Map[256], * pPrev, * pMemory;
4546  char * pSopSizes, ** pSops;
4547  int i, k, b, Size;
4548 
4549  // map chars into their numbers
4550  for ( i = 0; i < 256; i++ )
4551  Map[i] = (char)(-1);
4552  for ( i = 0; i < 81; i++ )
4553  Map[(int)s_Data3[i]] = (char)i;
4554 
4555  // count the number of strings
4556  for ( Size = 0; s_Data4[Size] && Size < 100000; Size++ );
4557  assert( Size < 100000 );
4558 
4559  // allocate memory
4560  pMemory = ABC_ALLOC( char, Size * 75 );
4561  // copy the array into memory
4562  for ( i = 0; i < Size; i++ )
4563  for ( k = 0; k < 75; k++ )
4564  if ( s_Data4[i][k] == ' ' )
4565  pMemory[i*75+k] = (char)(-1);
4566  else
4567  pMemory[i*75+k] = Map[(int)s_Data4[i][k]];
4568 
4569  // set pointers and compute SOP sizes
4570  pSopSizes = ABC_ALLOC( char, 65536 );
4571  pSops = ABC_ALLOC( char *, 65536 );
4572  pSopSizes[0] = 0;
4573  pSops[0] = NULL;
4574  pPrev = pMemory;
4575  for ( k = 0, i = 1; i < 65536; k++ )
4576  if ( pMemory[k] == (char)(-1) )
4577  {
4578  pSopSizes[i] = pMemory + k - pPrev;
4579  pSops[i++] = pPrev;
4580  pPrev = pMemory + k + 1;
4581  }
4582  *ppSopSizes = pSopSizes;
4583  *ppSops = pSops;
4584 
4585  // verify the results - derive truth table from SOP
4586  for ( i = 1; i < 65536; i++ )
4587  {
4588  int uTruth = 0, uCube, Lit;
4589  for ( k = 0; k < pSopSizes[i]; k++ )
4590  {
4591  uCube = 0xFFFF;
4592  Lit = pSops[i][k];
4593  for ( b = 3; b >= 0; b-- )
4594  {
4595  if ( Lit % 3 == 0 )
4596  uCube &= uMasks[b][0];
4597  else if ( Lit % 3 == 1 )
4598  uCube &= uMasks[b][1];
4599  Lit = Lit / 3;
4600  }
4601  uTruth |= uCube;
4602  }
4603  assert( uTruth == i );
4604  }
4605 }
4606

4608 
4609 /**Function*************************************************************
4610 
4611  Synopsis []
4612 
4613  Description []
4614 
4615  SideEffects []
4616 
4617  SeeAlso []
4618 
4619 ***********************************************************************/
4620 int Aig_ManDeriveCnfTest()
4621 {
4622  int i, k, Lit;
4623  printf( "\n" );
4624  for ( i = 80; i >= 0; i-- )
4625  {
4626  Lit = i;
4627  for ( k = 0; k < 4; k++ )
4628  {
4629  if ( Lit % 3 == 0 )
4630  printf( "%c", 'A' + k );
4631  else if ( Lit % 3 == 1 )
4632  printf( "%c", 'a' + k );
4633  Lit = Lit / 3;
4634  }
4635  printf( "\n" );
4636  }
4637 }

4643  Description []

4647  SeeAlso []

4649 ***********************************************************************/
4650 int Aig_ManDeriveCnfTest2()
4651 {
4652  char s_Data3[81] = "!#&()*+,-.0123456789:;<=>?ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ[]abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz|";
4653 
4654  unsigned uMasks[4][2] = {
4655  { 0x5555, 0xAAAA },
4656  { 0x3333, 0xCCCC },
4657  { 0x0F0F, 0xF0F0 },
4658  { 0x00FF, 0xFF00 }

4660  char Buffer[100], * pCur;
4661  FILE * pFile;

4671  pFile = fopen( "cands2.txt", "r" );
4672  while ( fgets( Buffer, 100, pFile ) )

4675  Extra_ReadHexadecimal( &uTruth2, Buffer+2, 4 );
4676  else
4677  uTruth2 = 0xFFFFFF;
4678 
4679  // skip all chars till a-d or A-D
4680  if ( Buffer[0] == '0' )
4681  for ( pCur = Buffer; *pCur != '\n'; pCur++ )
4682  {
4683 // if ( *pCur >= 'a' && *pCur <= 'd' || *pCur >= 'A' && *pCur <= 'D' )
4684  if ( *pCur == ':' )
4685  {
4686  pCur++;
4687  break;
4688  }
4689  }
4690  else
4691  pCur = Buffer;
4692 
4693 
4694  uTruth = 0;
4695  CountCur = 0;
4696  uCube = 0xFFFF;
4697  for ( i = 0; i < 4; i++ )
4698  Cube[i] = 2;
4699 
4700  for ( ; *pCur; pCur++ )
4701  {
4702  if ( *pCur == '+' || *pCur == '\n' )
4703  {
4704  uTruth |= uCube;
4705  uCube = 0xFFFF;
4706 
4707  // get the cube
4708  cCube = 0;
4709  for ( i = 0; i < 4; i++ )
4710  cCube = 3 * cCube + Cube[i];
4711  for ( i = 0; i < 4; i++ )
4712  Cube[i] = 2;
4713 
4714  assert( cCube >= 0 && cCube < 81 );
4715  Sop[CountCur] = cCube;
4716  CountCur++;
4717  if ( *pCur == '\n' )
4718  {
4719  Sop[CountCur] = 0;
4720  break;
4721  }
4722  }
4723  else if ( *pCur >= 'a' && *pCur <= 'd' )
4724  {
4725  uCube &= uMasks[*pCur-'a'][1];
4726  Cube[*pCur-'a'] = 1;
4727  }
4728  else if ( *pCur >= 'A' && *pCur <= 'D' )
4729  {
4730  uCube &= uMasks[*pCur-'A'][0];
4731  Cube[*pCur-'A'] = 0;
4732  }
4733  }
4734  assert( *pCur == '\n' );
4735  assert( uTruth2 == 0xFFFFFF || uTruth2 == uTruth );
4736 
4737  Counter += CountCur;
4738  pNums[uTruth] = CountCur;
4739  pSops[uTruth] = ALLOC( char, CountCur );
4740  memcpy( pSops[uTruth], Sop, CountCur );
4741  pLines[nLines++] = Counter;
4742  }
4743  fclose( pFile );
4744 
4745  printf( "Lines = %d. Counter = %d.\n", nLines, Counter );
